CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1945, pg. 20, reads: "Jump Artist - Will Hitchcock and his orchestra will invade the Roxian Gardens on Friday, May 11, for one swing-soaked night, under the banner of the Jocose Club. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Will Hitchcock wearing moustache, dark double breasted pinstriped suit, and patterned tie, posed in front of light colored background, in Harris Studio
